ust_2018()`, `at_least_rust_2021()`\n- Symbol mappings for each edition to prelude modules\n\n### Key Differences Between Editions\n\n**2015 Edition**:\n- Crate-relative imports by default\n- `use foo;` prepends crate root internally\n- `::foo` resolves from crate root\n- Prelude: v1 only\n\n**2018 Edition**:\n- Module-relative imports (uniform paths)\n- `use foo;` looks in current module, not crate root\n- `::foo` refers to extern prelude (no crate root fallback)\n- Prelude: v1 (via rust_2018 re-export)\n- Deprecated: `#[macro_use] extern crate`\n\n**2021 Edition**:\n- Inherits 2018 import behavior\n- Prelude: v1 + `FromIterator`, `TryFrom`, `TryInto`\n- Removes some macros from prelude (e.g., `try!`)\n\n**2024 Edition**:\n- Inherits 2021 behavior\n- Prelude: v1 + 2021 items + `Future`, `IntoFuture`\n- Additional method resolution changes\n"
