  "text": "## Edition-Specific Import Path Handling in Rust\n\nThis analysis identifies all Rust source files in rust-lang/rust (github.com/sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7) that implement edition-specific import path handling.\n\n### Prelude Modules (Edition-Specific Exports)\n\nThe standard library and core implement edition-specific prelude modules that control which items are automatically available:\n\n**Core Prelude** (library/core/src/prelude/mod.rs):\n- Defines `v1` module as the base prelude\n- `rust_2015` and `rust_2018` re-export v1\n- `rust_2021` adds `FromIterator`, `TryFrom`, and `TryInto`\n- `rust_2024` adds `Future` and `IntoFuture` in addition to 2021 items\n- `rust_future` (unstable) provides future prelude items\n\n**Standard Library Prelude** (library/std/src/prelude/mod.rs):\n- Mirrors core prelude structure\n- `rust_2021` re-exports core::prelude::rust_2021 items\n- `rust_2024` re-exports core::prelude::rust_2024 items\n\n**Prelude v1** (library/core/src/prelude/v1.rs and library/std/src/prelude/v1.rs):\n- Base set of items available in all editions\n- Common across 2015, 2018, 2021, 2024\n- Includes markers, operators, functions, and core types\n\n### Standard Library Imports Injection\n\n**compiler/rustc_builtin_macros/src/standard_library_imports.rs**:\n- The `inject()` function is the central point that automatically injects prelude imports for each crate\n- Edition-aware selection of prelude: uses `Edition2015`, `Edition2018`, `Edition2021`, `Edition2024`, or `EditionFuture`\n- Constructs import path with edition suffix (e.g., `std::prelude::rust_2021`)\n- Adds `#[macro_use] extern crate std/core` at crate root\n- Uses different span contexts (def_site vs call_site) based on edition >= 2018\n\n### Resolver Implementation (Edition-Specific Path Resolution)\n\n**compiler/rustc_resolve/src/build_reduced_graph.rs**:\n- `build_reduced_graph_for_use_tree()`: Handles import path construction with edition-specific rules\n  - 2015 edition: prepends crate root to imports (e.g., `foo` becomes `::foo`)\n  - 2018+ edition: uses extern prelude for `::foo` syntax\n  - Checks span edition via `is_rust_2015()` for lazy root prepending\n- `try_resolve_visibility()`: Handles visibility paths with edition differences\n  - 2015: visibility paths are crate-relative by default\n  - 2018+: visibility paths are module-relative\n- `process_macro_use_imports()`: Processes `#[macro_use]` attributes on extern crates\n- Virtual `ModuleAndExternPrelude`: Used for 2015 edition macros on 2018+ codebases\n\n**compiler/rustc_resolve/src/ident.rs**:\n- `resolve_ident_in_module()`: Resolves identifiers with scope consideration\n- Handles 2015 macros expanding in 2018+ codebases (lines 1791-1797)\n- Special case: `::a::b` from 2015 macro on 2018 global edition\n\n**compiler/rustc_resolve/src/lib.rs**:\n- `extern_prelude`: IndexMap storing external crate items\n- `ExternPreludeEntry`: Tracks both item and flag bindings for extern crates\n- Two scopes: `ExternPreludeItems` and `ExternPreludeFlags` for name resolution\n\n**compiler/rustc_resolve/src/imports.rs**:\n- Import data structure with `ModuleOrUniformRoot`:\n  - `ModuleAndExternPrelude`: special case for 2015 edition `use ::foo`\n  - `ExternPrelude`: for 2018+ editions\n- Handles reexport checking and visibility violations\n\n**compiler/rustc_resolve/src/macros.rs**:\n- Macro resolution with edition awareness\n- Handles extern crate compilation with edition parameter\n\n**compiler/rustc_resolve/src/diagnostics.rs**:\n- Edition-aware error messages for path resolution\n- Line 2483: special handling for `::foo` based on `sess.edition() > Edition::Edition2015`\n\n**compiler/rustc_resolve/src/check_unused.rs**:\n- Lint for unused `#[macro_use]` imports\n- Handles `MACRO_USE_EXTERN_CRATE` lint for 2018+ editions\n\n### Edition Definition\n\n**compiler/rustc_span/src/edition.rs**:\n- `Edition` enum: `Edition2015`, `Edition2018`, `Edition2021`, `Edition2024`, `EditionFuture`\n- Methods: `at_least_rust_2018()`, `at_least_rust_2021()`\n- Symbol mappings for each edition to prelude modules\n\n### Key Differences Between Editions\n\n**2015 Edition**:\n- Crate-relative imports by default\n- `use foo;` prepends crate root internally\n- `::foo` resolves from crate root\n- Prelude: v1 only\n\n**2018 Edition**:\n- Module-relative imports (uniform paths)\n- `use foo;` looks in current module, not crate root\n- `::foo` refers to extern prelude (no crate root fallback)\n- Prelude: v1 (via rust_2018 re-export)\n- Deprecated: `#[macro_use] extern crate`\n\n**2021 Edition**:\n- Inherits 2018 import behavior\n- Prelude: v1 + `FromIterator`, `TryFrom`, `TryInto`\n- Removes some macros from prelude (e.g., `try!`)\n\n**2024 Edition**:\n- Inherits 2021 behavior\n- Prelude: v1 + 2021 items + `Future`, `IntoFuture`\n- Additional method resolution changes\n"
